-- Lion Capital, Permira May Bid for Unilever's Findus Italy Unit, FT Reports
-- Anna Stablum
-- 2010-07-10T09:34:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-10/lion-capital-permira-may-bid-for-unilever-s-findus-italy-unit-ft-reports.html

          
          
             Unilever Plc  may receive a bid for
its Italian frozen-food business Findus Italy from private
equity group Lion Capital, the  Financial Times  reported, citing
unidentified people close to the process.  
 Lion wants to integrate the business into Findus Group,
which it bought in 2008 for 1.1 billion pounds ($1.66 billion),
the newspaper said.  
 Unilever may also receive bids for Findus Italy from BC
Partners and Permira by a July 13 deadline. The unit may sell
for 800 million euros ($1.01 billion).  
